quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  54,1,The Hour has drawn near and the moon is split
  54,2,"If they see a sign, they turn away, and say, ‘An incessant magic!’"
  54,3,"They denied and followed their own desires, and every matter has a setting [appropriate to it]"
  54,4,There have already come to them reports containing admonishment
  54,5,"[and representing] far-reaching wisdom; but warnings are of no avail"
  54,6,So turn away from them! The day when the Caller calls to a dire thing
  54,7,"they will emerge from the graves as if they were scattered locusts with a humbled look [in their eyes]"
  54,8,"scrambling toward the summoner. The faithless will say, ‘This is a hard day!’"
  54,9,"The people of Noah impugned before them. So they impugned Our servant and said, ‘A crazy man,’ and he was reviled"
  54,10,"Thereat he invoked his Lord, [saying,] ‘I have been overcome, so help [me].’"
  54,11,Then We opened the gates of the sky with pouring waters
  54,12,"and We made the earth burst forth with springs, and the waters met for a preordained purpose"
  54,13,We bore him on a vessel made of planks and nails
  54,14,"which sailed [over the flood waters] in Our sight, as a retribution for him who was met with disbelief"
  54,15,Certainly We have left it as a sign; so is there anyone who will be admonished
  54,16,So how were My punishment and warnings
  54,17,Certainly We have made the Quran simple for the sake of admonishment. So is there anyone who will be admonished
  54,18,"[The people of] ‘Ad impugned [their apostle]. So how were My punishment and warnings"
  54,19,Indeed We unleashed upon them an icy gale on an incessantly ill-fated day
  54,20,knocking down people as if they were trunks of uprooted palm trees
  54,21,So how were My punishment and warnings
  54,22,Certainly We have made the Quran simple for the sake of admonishment. So is there anyone who will be admonished